d himself on the Potomac River in what was then Stafford County, VA, as a planter and exporter. He also practiced law, was a member of the Virginia House of Burgesses, and served in 1687 as lieutenant colonel of the county militia."],"variants":[{"name":"Fitz","meanings":["English: from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (from Latin <i>filius</i>), used originally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same personal name and then conventionalized as a hereditary surname, or short for a surname of which <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ was the first element, for example   Fitzhenry   and   Fitzroy  .","Altered form of English   Fitch  .","German: from a vernacular pet form of the personal name <i>Vinzenz</i> (see   Vincent  ) or <i>Vitus</i> (see   Vito  , compare   Veit  ). Compare also   Fietz  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":42,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":51,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":86,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs John FitzHugh was born about 1173, in England. She had at least 1 daughter with John FitzHugh of Lithrogg."},"et":{"about 1173–":"umbes 1173–Surnud","1166–Male":"1166–Surnud","1194–Female":"1194–Surnud","1173–Female":"1173–Surnud","about 1173":"umbes 1173","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1166":"1166","1173":"1173","1194":"1194","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"Malpas, Cheshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1173–":"noin 1173–Kuollut","1166–Male":"1166–Kuollut","1194–Female":"1194–Kuollut","1173–Female":"1173–Kuollut","about 1173":"noin 1173","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1166":"1166","1173":"1173","1194":"1194","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"Malpas, Cheshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1173–":"environ 1173–Décédée","1166–Male":"1166–Décédé","1194–Female":"1194–Décédée","1173–Female":"1173–Décédée","about 1173":"environ 1173","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1166":"1166","1173":"1173","1194":"1194","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"Malpas, Cheshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs John FitzHugh est née environ 1173, à Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec John FitzHugh of Lithrogg."},"de":{"about 1173–":"um 1173–Verstorben","1166–Male":"1166–Verstorben","1194–Female":"1194–Verstorben","1173–Female":"1173–Verstorben","about 1173":"um 1173","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1166":"1166","1173":"1173","1194":"1194","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"Malpas, Cheshire, England","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Mrs John FitzHugh wurde um 1173 in England geboren. Sie hatte mit John FitzHugh of Lithrogg mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"about 1173–":"about 1173–Desede","1166